{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/37095.The_Shell_Seekers", "title": "The Shell Seekers", "titleComplete": "The Shell Seekers", "description": "Artist's daughter Penelope Keeling can look back on a full and varied life: a Bohemian childhood in London and Cornwall, an unhappy wartime marriage, and the one man she truly loved. She has brought up three children - and learned to accept them as they are. Yet she is far too energetic and independent to settle sweetly into pensioned-off old-age. And when she discovers that her most treasured possession, her father's painting, The Shell Seekers, is now worth a small fortune, it is Penelope who must make the decisions that will determine whether her family can continue to survive as a family, or be split apart.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1385213408i/37095.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Historical", "British Literature", "Fiction", "Contemporary", "Chick Lit", "Novels", "Adult Fiction", "Family", "Romance"], "asin": "051722285X", "isbn": "051722285X", "isbn13": "9780517222850", "publisher": "Gramercy", "author": ["Rosamunde Pilcher"], "publishDate": 1081234800000, "characters": ["Penelope Keeling"], "places": ["England", "London, England", "Cornwall, England"], "ratingHistogram": [1386, 3895, 18262, 36091, 50706], "ratingsCount": 110340, "reviewsCount": 4581, "numPages": 544, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50365.A_Suitable_Boy", "title": "A Suitable Boy", "titleComplete": "A Suitable Boy (A Bridge of Leaves, #1)", "description": "Vikram Seth's novel is, at its core, a love story: Lata and her mother, Mrs. Rupa Mehra, are both trying to find\u2014through love or through exacting maternal appraisal\u2014a suitable boy for Lata to marry. Set in the early 1950s, in an India newly independent and struggling through a time of crisis, A Suitable Boy takes us into the richly imagined world of four large extended families and spins a compulsively readable tale of their lives and loves. A sweeping panoramic portrait of a complex, multiethnic society in flux, A Suitable Boy remains the story of ordinary people caught up in a web of love and ambition, humor and sadness, prejudice and reconciliation, the most delicate social etiquette and the most appalling violence.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1329421639i/50365.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Historical", "Fiction", "India", "Novels", "Indian Literature", "Classics", "Romance", "Literature", "Asia"], "asin": "0060786523", "isbn": "0060786523", "isbn13": "9780060786526", "publisher": "Harper Perennial Modern Classics", "series": ["A Bridge of Leaves"], "author": ["Vikram Seth"], "publishDate": 1128409200000, "characters": ["Varun Mehra", "Pran Kapoor", "Amit Chatterji", "Savita Mehra", "Arun Mehra", "Lata Mehra", "Meenakshi Mehra (n\u00e9e Chatterji)", "Maan Kapoor", "Rupa Mehra"], "places": ["Brahmapur", "Calcutta", "Delhi", "India", "Kanpur"], "ratingHistogram": [901, 2134, 7931, 16502, 20540], "ratingsCount": 48008, "reviewsCount": 2995, "numPages": 1474, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "WH Smith Literary Award", "awardedAt": 757411200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Commonwealth Writers' Prize", "awardedAt": 757411200000, "category": "Best Book Overall", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2998.The_Secret_Garden", "title": "The Secret Garden", "titleComplete": "The Secret Garden", "description": "In a house full of sadness and secrets, can young, orphaned Mary find happiness?Mary Lennox, a spoiled, ill-tempered, and unhealthy child, comes to live with her reclusive uncle in Misselthwaite Manor on England\u2019s Yorkshire moors after the death of her parents. There she meets a hearty housekeeper and her spirited brother, a dour gardener, a cheerful robin, and her wilful, hysterical, and sickly cousin, Master Colin, whose wails she hears echoing through the house at night.With the help of the robin, Mary finds the door to a secret garden, neglected and hidden for years. When she decides to restore the garden in secret, the story becomes a charming journey into the places of the heart, where faith restores health, flowers refresh the spirit, and the magic of the garden, coming to life anew, brings health to Colin and happiness to Mary.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327873635i/2998.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Childrens", "Historical", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Classics", "Audiobook", "Literature"], "asin": "0517189607", "isbn": "0517189607", "isbn13": "9780517189603", "publisher": "Children's Classics", "author": ["Frances Hodgson Burnett"], "publishDate": 904633200000, "characters": ["Mary Lennox", "Mrs. Medlock", "Dr. Craven", "Ben Weatherstaff", "Dickon Sowerby", "Susan Sowerby", "Archibald Craven", "Martha Sowerby", "Colin Craven"], "places": ["England", "Yorkshire, England"], "ratingHistogram": [15890, 41641, 199171, 393577, 511936], "ratingsCount": 1162215, "reviewsCount": 28141, "numPages": 331, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Lewis Carroll Shelf Award", "awardedAt": -378662400000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15823480-anna-karenina", "title": "Anna Karenina", "titleComplete": "Anna Karenina", "description": "Acclaimed by many as the world's greatest novel, Anna Karenina provides a vast panorama of contemporary life in Russia and of humanity in general. In it Tolstoy uses his intense imaginative insight to create some of the most memorable characters in all of literature. Anna is a sophisticated woman who abandons her empty existence as the wife of Karenin and turns to Count Vronsky to fulfil her passionate nature - with tragic consequences. Levin is a reflection of Tolstoy himself, often expressing the author's own views and convictions.Throughout, Tolstoy points no moral, merely inviting us not to judge but to watch. As Rosemary Edmonds comments, 'He leaves the shifting patterns of the kaleidoscope to bring home the meaning of the brooding words following the title, 'Vengeance is mine, and I will repay.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1546091617i/15823480.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Russia", "Historical", "Fiction", "Russian Literature", "Novels", "Classics", "Romance", "Literature", "19th Century"], "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["Lev Tolstoj", "Louise Maude", "Bruno Goetz", "L\u00e9on Tolsto\u00ef", "Dieter Wellershoff", "Leo Tolstoy", "Aylmer Maude"], "publishDate": 1350370800000, "characters": ["Prince Stepan \"Stiva\" Arkadyevitch Oblonsky", "Anna Arkadyevna Karenina", "Princess Ekaterina \"Kitty\" Aleksandrovna Shcherbatskaya", "Konstantin \"Kostya\" Dmitrievitch Levin", "Count Aleksei Kirillovich Vronsky"], "places": ["Russia"], "ratingHistogram": [19664, 42285, 143076, 276067, 361729], "ratingsCount": 842821, "reviewsCount": 35017, "numPages": 964, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Premio literatura rusa en Espa\u00f1a", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Read Russia Prize", "awardedAt": 1